WEBVTT

00:00:20.729 --> 00:00:25.775
<i>I put my hands together and pray</i>

00:00:25.859 --> 00:00:31.031
<i>Why is fate so cruel?</i>

00:00:31.114 --> 00:00:36.536
<i>My will to put on a brave face
is about to break</i>

00:00:36.619 --> 00:00:41.708
<i>Everything I do seems to go wrong,
you know?</i>

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:44.544
<i>Oh, calm down,
I still have faith in you</i>

00:00:44.586 --> 00:00:47.380
<i>Even if we're apart</i>

00:00:47.464 --> 00:00:54.637
<i>Even if you forget about me someday</i>

00:00:55.597 --> 00:00:57.390
BLEACH: THOUSAND-YEAR BLOOD WAR

00:00:58.099 --> 00:01:00.393
<i>We don't need words
to understand each other</i>

00:01:00.477 --> 00:01:03.354
<i>We're connected on a higher level</i>

00:01:03.438 --> 00:01:08.276
<i>I'm sorry, fate,
but you're full of it</i>

00:01:08.401 --> 00:01:10.904
<i>So let's laugh it off
by putting on a brave face</i>

00:01:10.987 --> 00:01:18.536
<i>With you, I think we can alter fate</i>

00:01:18.912 --> 00:01:24.167
<i>On lonely nights
when I feel like crying</i>

00:01:24.250 --> 00:01:27.962
<i>I will pray for you</i>

00:01:28.088 --> 00:01:30.924
<i>so that I won't leave you all alone</i>

00:01:55.949 --> 00:01:58.993
I will take the Soul King's place.

00:01:59.327 --> 00:02:00.870
Is that even possible?!

00:02:01.371 --> 00:02:02.747
I'll explain later.

00:02:12.298 --> 00:02:13.299
That's...!

00:02:13.466 --> 00:02:14.717
It's the one from...

00:02:14.801 --> 00:02:16.261
Captain Ukitake?

00:02:21.057 --> 00:02:23.184
Mimihagi, Mimihagi...

00:02:23.560 --> 00:02:27.897
Open the power of your eye that
you placed inside of my organs.

00:02:27.939 --> 00:02:30.191
Forsake my organs
and open your eye.

00:02:30.608 --> 00:02:32.819
- Mimihagi, Mimihagi...
- <i>Mimihagi, Mimihagi...</i>

00:02:32.944 --> 00:02:35.113
Kill the illness
eating away our child,

00:02:35.155 --> 00:02:37.323
and devour his organs.

00:02:37.657 --> 00:02:41.953
RUKON DISTRICT –
EAST 76 DISTRICT, "SAKAHONE"

00:02:37.824 --> 00:02:39.826
Mimihagi, Mimihagi...

00:02:39.951 --> 00:02:41.953
The divine hand from the heavens...

00:02:42.078 --> 00:02:44.164
please bless us with your power...

00:02:44.664 --> 00:02:46.833
Mimihagi, Mimihagi...

00:02:46.916 --> 00:02:49.294
Kill the illness
eating away our child,

00:02:49.335 --> 00:02:51.254
and devour his organs.

00:02:51.796 --> 00:02:53.882
Mimihagi, Mimihagi...

00:02:54.048 --> 00:02:56.134
The divine hand from the heavens...

00:02:56.176 --> 00:02:58.511
please bless us with your power...

00:02:58.928 --> 00:03:01.014
Mimihagi, Mimihagi...

00:03:01.181 --> 00:03:03.308
Kill the illness
eating away our child,

00:03:03.433 --> 00:03:05.476
and devour his organs.

00:03:05.935 --> 00:03:07.979
- Mimihagi, Mimihagi...
- Jushiro!

00:03:08.146 --> 00:03:09.856
The divine hand from the heavens...

00:03:09.939 --> 00:03:11.816
please bless us with your power...

00:03:14.027 --> 00:03:18.448
Mimihagi,
please save our child Jushiro!

00:03:18.865 --> 00:03:22.202
Grant our three-year-old
the joy of living!

00:03:22.994 --> 00:03:23.786
We beg of you!

00:03:24.204 --> 00:03:29.292
Jushiro... I'm sorry
I didn't bear you healthy...

00:03:29.918 --> 00:03:30.877
I'm so sorry...

00:03:36.424 --> 00:03:39.636
Mother... Don't cry.

00:04:49.038 --> 00:04:50.373
Jushiro!

00:04:55.586 --> 00:04:56.671
Jushiro...!

00:04:59.215 --> 00:05:04.804
<i>On that stormy night,
Mimihagi saved my life...</i>

00:05:11.394 --> 00:05:12.353
Hello.

00:05:13.313 --> 00:05:15.606
Watch where you're going, hag!

00:05:16.107 --> 00:05:18.943
Well? Aren't you gonna apologize
for bumping into me?

00:05:19.402 --> 00:05:21.779
My sleeve barely touched you...

00:05:22.113 --> 00:05:24.115
Stop exaggerating.

00:05:24.574 --> 00:05:25.950
What was that?

00:05:27.368 --> 00:05:28.578
No, don't do it.

00:05:29.495 --> 00:05:30.997
And who are you
supposed to be?

00:05:31.039 --> 00:05:32.999
You taking this hag's side—?

00:05:38.254 --> 00:05:40.965
Don't underestimate me
just because I'm old.

00:05:42.967 --> 00:05:46.179
Are you okay?
I did try to warn you.

00:05:46.804 --> 00:05:49.724
Ms. Oyone has quite the reputation
in these parts.

00:05:49.891 --> 00:05:51.934
She's a fireball.

00:05:52.643 --> 00:05:55.229
Oyone or whatever her name is...

00:05:55.313 --> 00:05:57.815
Next time I see her,
I'll kick her ass.

00:05:59.525 --> 00:06:01.319
If you're looking
to blow off steam,

00:06:01.361 --> 00:06:03.863
then come and join me
at the Soul Reaper Academy.

00:06:04.113 --> 00:06:05.073
What?

00:06:05.490 --> 00:06:07.116
If you become a squad member,

00:06:07.200 --> 00:06:10.620
then you'll get paid for fighting
and people will thank you for it.

00:06:10.787 --> 00:06:11.954
It's killing two birds
with one stone.

00:06:12.205 --> 00:06:13.956
Piss off!

00:06:18.628 --> 00:06:21.214
I'm Jushiro Ukitake.
What's your name?

00:06:23.841 --> 00:06:25.968
L-Let go of me!

00:06:28.429 --> 00:06:29.847
You'll pay for that!

00:06:30.515 --> 00:06:32.100
Okay! Looking forward to it.

00:06:32.475 --> 00:06:33.476
See ya.

00:06:49.951 --> 00:06:53.913
Don't overdo yourself, Ukitake...

00:07:01.170 --> 00:07:02.213
Begin!

00:07:09.804 --> 00:07:11.722
They have good form.

00:07:12.265 --> 00:07:15.685
They're still green,
but they have potential.

00:07:33.619 --> 00:07:34.620
That's enough.

00:07:38.833 --> 00:07:40.334
Not bad, buddy.

00:07:41.085 --> 00:07:43.796
No mercy even against
a sickly person, huh?

00:07:44.797 --> 00:07:46.466
I'm Jushiro Ukitake.

00:07:46.966 --> 00:07:48.259
Shunsui Kyoraku.

00:07:48.634 --> 00:07:49.635
I know.

00:07:49.886 --> 00:07:50.887
Thought so.

00:07:51.053 --> 00:07:55.183
I could always feel you
staring at me during class.

00:07:56.851 --> 00:07:57.935
Was it that obvious?

00:07:58.769 --> 00:08:01.689
The truth is,
I have a huge favor to ask of you.

00:08:02.190 --> 00:08:03.191
Huh?

00:08:05.443 --> 00:08:07.987
So you were after
my monaka sweets, eh?

00:08:08.362 --> 00:08:11.365
I've been asked to
introduce people to girls,

00:08:11.449 --> 00:08:14.035
but never to a sweets shop.

00:08:15.786 --> 00:08:17.788
You always looked happy
while eating it,

00:08:17.914 --> 00:08:19.290
so it got me curious.

00:08:19.832 --> 00:08:22.460
That's because the monaka sweets
here use sake lees.

00:08:22.543 --> 00:08:23.920
Wait, it has alcohol in it?!

00:08:24.003 --> 00:08:25.588
Is that a problem?

00:08:26.005 --> 00:08:27.006
Yes, a big one!

00:08:28.591 --> 00:08:31.677
- Big Brother!
- Big Brother.

00:08:33.971 --> 00:08:35.932
Yes! You brought us monaka sweets!

00:08:36.015 --> 00:08:38.226
No! That's not good for children.

00:08:39.393 --> 00:08:41.354
- Look, you can't eat these...
- My bad.

00:08:52.865 --> 00:08:54.534
I want to show you something.

00:08:58.204 --> 00:08:59.205
Is that...

00:08:59.789 --> 00:09:05.920
Mimihagi, the local deity of
East 76 Rukon District, Sakahone.

00:09:06.379 --> 00:09:09.840
Mimihagi... so it really does exist.

00:09:10.633 --> 00:09:11.634
You've heard of it?

00:09:12.176 --> 00:09:15.596
There are rumors among
the upper noble clans.

00:09:16.180 --> 00:09:19.183
They say that long ago,
a divine power of the Soul King

00:09:19.267 --> 00:09:21.394
got detached and
fell from the heavens.

00:09:21.894 --> 00:09:23.646
A divine power of the Soul King?

00:09:23.854 --> 00:09:25.189
Doesn't make sense, right?

00:09:25.815 --> 00:09:28.234
The Soul King is still
at the Royal Palace.

00:09:28.985 --> 00:09:31.529
But seeing this Mimihagi,

00:09:31.571 --> 00:09:34.699
I'm starting to think
those rumors were true.

00:09:36.450 --> 00:09:38.035
Take a look at this figure.

00:09:38.244 --> 00:09:41.831
The eye catches your attention,
but it's shaped more like a...

00:09:43.249 --> 00:09:48.004
The body of the Soul King
is said to bring many blessings.

00:09:48.588 --> 00:09:53.593
The left hand controls advancement.
The right hand...

00:09:53.884 --> 00:09:55.970
Stillness, right?

00:09:56.053 --> 00:09:57.847
Oh? So you know?

00:09:59.724 --> 00:10:01.183
No, but I did have a feeling.

00:10:01.934 --> 00:10:05.563
I managed to survive
thanks to Mimihagi,

00:10:05.605 --> 00:10:07.565
but my illness hasn't gone away.

00:10:10.276 --> 00:10:11.777
I bet you started believing
in those rumors

00:10:11.902 --> 00:10:13.946
after you heard about me,
didn't you?

00:10:14.780 --> 00:10:16.949
I poked my nose
where I shouldn't have...

00:10:17.533 --> 00:10:18.576
I'm sorry.

00:10:19.285 --> 00:10:20.620
But you're not going to tell me

00:10:20.745 --> 00:10:23.080
to give up on joining
the 13 Court Guard Squads

00:10:23.164 --> 00:10:25.499
because of that are you, Shunsui?

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:28.878
I won't let you die that easily,
Jushiro.

00:10:35.509 --> 00:10:37.303
You do not wish to appoint
a new lieutenant?!

00:10:37.637 --> 00:10:39.972
Correct.
No one can ever replace Kaien.

00:10:40.556 --> 00:10:45.186
We understand you were born with
an incurable lung disease.

00:10:45.436 --> 00:10:49.690
We've heard you even had an episode
while battling the Hollow.

00:10:49.815 --> 00:10:51.984
Yes, you heard correctly.

00:10:52.360 --> 00:10:55.863
That is all the more reason
you need a lieutenant.

00:10:55.988 --> 00:10:58.491
We cannot comply with your request!

00:10:58.866 --> 00:11:00.785
"The power to appoint
someone to lieutenant

00:11:00.826 --> 00:11:01.869
lies with their squad captain."

00:11:02.578 --> 00:11:05.164
That was a decision
made by your people.

00:11:06.791 --> 00:11:10.002
If I cannot handle it alone,
then I will die a quick death.

00:11:10.836 --> 00:11:14.965
After that, you can install
the captain of your choice.

00:11:15.966 --> 00:11:17.885
I won't die so easily, though.

00:11:21.806 --> 00:11:23.015
I heard the news.

00:11:23.391 --> 00:11:27.978
Seems you gave Central 46 an earful
about not needing a lieutenant, eh?

00:11:28.854 --> 00:11:31.357
If it were me,
I'd want at least two or more...

00:11:31.816 --> 00:11:34.026
with the condition of
being cute girls, that is.

00:11:35.695 --> 00:11:39.990
Ukitake... There comes a time
to put your life on the line.

00:11:40.574 --> 00:11:42.827
This wasn't your time, that's all.

00:11:43.994 --> 00:11:47.873
For now,
let's mourn for Kaien's death.

00:11:50.584 --> 00:11:53.713
Unfortunately,
Nanao hid my sake, so...

00:12:04.098 --> 00:12:08.769
Old Man Yama sure picked
one hell of a time to die on us.

00:12:09.437 --> 00:12:14.150
I never knew giving out orders
as head captain felt this horrible.

00:12:15.067 --> 00:12:18.529
If Old Man Yama were still alive,
I'd never have had to find out...

00:12:19.280 --> 00:12:23.033
Under better circumstances,
I'd be sharing a drink with you...

00:12:24.910 --> 00:12:28.914
Was there ever a time when drinking
helped ease your worries?

00:12:29.206 --> 00:12:30.207
Sure there was.

00:12:30.291 --> 00:12:34.003
Especially whenever
I got dumped by girls.

00:12:34.462 --> 00:12:37.506
Then you won't be needing
any drinks this time around.

00:12:38.382 --> 00:12:40.259
You have my full attention.

00:12:43.888 --> 00:12:47.057
If you don't mind...
I'd like to be alone for a moment.

00:12:49.935 --> 00:12:52.730
Farewell, Captain Ukitake.

00:12:55.900 --> 00:12:58.027
We'll see each other soon.

00:13:02.198 --> 00:13:04.450
Captain! We have an emergency!

00:13:04.784 --> 00:13:05.910
The Seireitei is...!

00:13:05.993 --> 00:13:07.328
Captain Ukitake!

00:13:07.453 --> 00:13:09.747
- Captain Ukitake!
- Mimihagi, Mimihagi...

00:13:09.955 --> 00:13:11.916
Open the power of your eye.

00:13:12.041 --> 00:13:14.084
Mimihagi, Mimihagi...

00:13:14.168 --> 00:13:15.920
Open the power of your eye.

00:13:16.712 --> 00:13:18.964
Open the power of your eye

00:13:19.006 --> 00:13:21.383
that you placed inside me
by forsaking my organs.

00:13:22.927 --> 00:13:24.053
What is that thing?!

00:13:31.143 --> 00:13:32.436
Captain Ukitake!

00:13:32.561 --> 00:13:33.562
As you were!

00:13:35.189 --> 00:13:39.193
The power of Mimihagi
was attached to my lungs.

00:13:40.110 --> 00:13:43.656
The ritual that expands that power
to all the organs of my body

00:13:43.781 --> 00:13:44.949
is called Kamikake.

00:13:46.283 --> 00:13:49.829
Every organ in my body
now belongs to Mimihagi.

00:13:50.704 --> 00:13:53.833
By giving all of my organs
to Mimihagi,

00:13:53.833 --> 00:13:55.918
I become the embodiment
of Mimihagi.

00:13:57.002 --> 00:14:00.923
I am now
the Soul King's right arm itself.

00:14:01.966 --> 00:14:03.300
Are you saying...

00:14:03.843 --> 00:14:06.512
you performed Kamikake
in anticipation of this moment?

00:14:06.846 --> 00:14:07.847
That's right.

00:14:08.597 --> 00:14:11.684
From the moment
I knew why I survived,

00:14:11.767 --> 00:14:13.978
I've thought about this day.

00:14:14.854 --> 00:14:17.022
Nothing would please me more...

00:14:17.022 --> 00:14:19.316
than to sacrifice this life
I once lost for the Court Guards.

00:14:19.942 --> 00:14:23.863
If you die,
what will become of Squad 13?

00:14:24.864 --> 00:14:26.156
I'm sorry, Kuchiki.

00:14:26.866 --> 00:14:29.827
Seems I'm always
making things hard for you.

00:14:30.828 --> 00:14:32.037
Captain Ukitake...

00:14:33.998 --> 00:14:34.999
Captain...

00:14:36.375 --> 00:14:37.334
Captain...

00:14:39.044 --> 00:14:40.337
Captain!

00:14:40.796 --> 00:14:42.590
There are two types of battles...!

00:14:44.258 --> 00:14:46.594
You understand, don't you, Kuchiki?

00:15:00.232 --> 00:15:01.317
<i>Jushiro...</i>

00:15:02.818 --> 00:15:04.361
<i>There are two types of battles.</i>

00:15:05.237 --> 00:15:07.865
<i>A battle to protect life...</i>

00:15:08.407 --> 00:15:10.868
<i>or a battle to defend honor.</i>

00:15:12.578 --> 00:15:13.871
<i>Then my battle is to...!</i>

00:15:17.458 --> 00:15:20.753
All right, let's have a talk...

00:15:21.837 --> 00:15:23.756
Sosuke Aizen.

00:15:24.006 --> 00:15:27.676
SOSUKE AIZEN

00:15:39.688 --> 00:15:43.067
Is there still a reason
for you to fight me?

00:15:43.859 --> 00:15:46.904
The Soul King was created
to stabilize the Soul Society,

00:15:47.029 --> 00:15:50.699
where great numbers of souls
pass through.

00:15:51.116 --> 00:15:52.910
Now that it is gone,

00:15:53.452 --> 00:15:56.246
the Soul Society,
the Precipice World,

00:15:56.330 --> 00:15:58.374
Hueco Mundo,
and the World of the Living

00:15:58.791 --> 00:16:00.793
will all cease to exist!

00:16:01.085 --> 00:16:03.754
All by your hand, Ichigo!

00:16:04.421 --> 00:16:06.590
I'll draw his attention.

00:16:06.674 --> 00:16:09.093
Use your powers
to restore the Soul King.

00:16:09.593 --> 00:16:10.594
Got it.

00:16:10.678 --> 00:16:12.179
Let's go, Sado, Ganju!

00:16:12.513 --> 00:16:13.514
Yeah!

00:16:13.597 --> 00:16:16.684
Hey, over here!
Catch us if you can!

00:16:16.684 --> 00:16:17.851
Seppa!

00:16:20.938 --> 00:16:24.024
Brazo Izquierdo Del Diablo!

00:16:25.192 --> 00:16:26.360
Raiohken!

00:16:29.947 --> 00:16:31.240
Sotenkishun!

00:16:35.160 --> 00:16:36.161
Did it work?

00:16:47.881 --> 00:16:49.383
How foolish.

00:16:49.842 --> 00:16:51.510
You thought a mere human

00:16:51.552 --> 00:16:54.555
could bring the Soul King
back to life?

00:16:55.472 --> 00:16:56.724
It cannot be done!

00:16:56.724 --> 00:16:58.684
Regardless of what powers you use,

00:16:58.726 --> 00:17:01.645
the Soul King can no longer
be resurrected.

00:17:04.732 --> 00:17:06.900
The Soul King's power is fading...

00:17:06.942 --> 00:17:08.902
Isn't there anything we can do?

00:17:18.787 --> 00:17:20.414
- Captain Ukitake!
- Mr. Ukitake!

00:17:29.089 --> 00:17:31.717
The tremor... has stopped!

00:17:40.100 --> 00:17:41.477
The Soul King...

00:17:42.311 --> 00:17:43.937
What is that thing?

00:17:44.938 --> 00:17:48.525
<i>So even Yhwach
didn't see that shadow coming?</i>

00:17:51.111 --> 00:17:53.864
Why didn't my eyes
foresee this future?

00:17:59.620 --> 00:18:00.829
Captain...

00:18:04.917 --> 00:18:05.959
How long will he last?

00:18:07.628 --> 00:18:09.046
I doubt this would be enough

00:18:09.129 --> 00:18:11.465
to make Ukitake a stand-in
for the Soul King.

00:18:12.007 --> 00:18:15.803
This stability will probably
only last while Ukitake is alive.

00:18:16.845 --> 00:18:17.930
How much time do we have?

00:18:18.263 --> 00:18:20.057
- C-Captain—!
- It's the truth.

00:18:20.349 --> 00:18:21.517
Isn't that right, Urahara?

00:18:22.434 --> 00:18:23.644
I don't know.

00:18:24.019 --> 00:18:29.149
This is the first time I've seen
or even heard of Kamikake.

00:18:30.025 --> 00:18:32.528
I couldn't fathom a guess
how long he'll last.

00:18:33.821 --> 00:18:39.243
What I do know is that we must
find a way to stabilize the world

00:18:39.827 --> 00:18:44.248
while Mr. Ukitake is standing in
for the Soul King.

00:18:45.791 --> 00:18:47.793
Tenshiheiso is ready, sir.

00:18:48.001 --> 00:18:49.002
We can begin.

00:18:49.670 --> 00:18:51.839
I really wish we could,

00:18:52.548 --> 00:18:54.133
but we don't have enough
Spiritual Pressure.

00:19:02.474 --> 00:19:04.726
You're not responding at all...

00:19:04.893 --> 00:19:08.063
Are you against communicating
via Spiritual Pressure?

00:19:08.814 --> 00:19:13.360
Or is this place making it
impossible even for you?

00:19:14.236 --> 00:19:16.155
These keys
can break your seal.

00:19:16.905 --> 00:19:20.325
I've been allowed to use
only three of them.

00:19:21.743 --> 00:19:23.745
First, I'll undo the seal
to your mouth.

00:19:24.288 --> 00:19:26.957
"MOUTH"

00:19:27.249 --> 00:19:29.710
Now you should be able to
talk with your mouth,

00:19:29.793 --> 00:19:31.295
not your Spiritual Pressure.

00:19:32.212 --> 00:19:34.882
Ordinarily, it would be a challenge
to even talk

00:19:35.048 --> 00:19:37.593
after having your mouth shut
for two years.

00:19:38.010 --> 00:19:40.179
But knowing you,
I'm sure that's not the case.

00:19:41.847 --> 00:19:42.890
You're right.

00:19:44.224 --> 00:19:45.392
<i>Impossible.</i>

00:19:45.726 --> 00:19:48.395
<i>I only removed the seal
on his mouth.</i>

00:19:51.815 --> 00:19:52.900
What's the matter?

00:19:53.734 --> 00:19:56.320
You still have two more keys
you can use, don't you?

00:19:56.987 --> 00:19:58.822
"LEFT EYE" / "ANKLES"

00:20:00.699 --> 00:20:02.367
That makes three.

00:20:03.285 --> 00:20:05.704
How does it feel
to have your left eye

00:20:05.787 --> 00:20:07.039
and both ankles freed?

00:20:07.748 --> 00:20:08.749
I see.

00:20:09.166 --> 00:20:11.084
It seems you haven't changed much.

00:20:11.710 --> 00:20:14.046
Not sure if I should take that
as a compliment.

00:20:15.631 --> 00:20:17.090
Do you want to leave here?

00:20:17.674 --> 00:20:20.594
I don't recall
asking to be let out.

00:20:21.220 --> 00:20:23.096
Would a man
who doesn't want to leave

00:20:23.222 --> 00:20:26.141
tell me to use
the remaining two keys?

00:20:26.892 --> 00:20:28.685
Would a man who doesn't
want to let me out

00:20:29.061 --> 00:20:31.772
come here with a key
embedded in his body?

00:20:32.147 --> 00:20:35.025
Well, well.
You saw right through me.

00:20:35.776 --> 00:20:40.113
As you say, embedding the key
to this Muken Prison in my heart

00:20:40.822 --> 00:20:42.783
was the condition
for me to come here

00:20:42.866 --> 00:20:45.285
and remove
three of your restraints.

00:20:45.869 --> 00:20:46.870
I see.

00:20:47.162 --> 00:20:48.664
So if you're killed,

00:20:48.664 --> 00:20:52.042
the gates to Muken
will be sealed for all eternity.

00:20:52.709 --> 00:20:55.754
They figured I would
go as far as killing you

00:20:55.879 --> 00:20:58.632
to get my hands on
that key to Muken.

00:20:59.633 --> 00:21:03.011
How typical of those Central 46...

00:21:03.512 --> 00:21:04.680
Now, now.

00:21:04.972 --> 00:21:09.851
I'm sure it's all because
they care about the Soul Society.

00:21:10.519 --> 00:21:12.229
Let's just leave it at that.

00:21:13.814 --> 00:21:15.899
Now then,
let's get down to business.

00:21:17.359 --> 00:21:21.071
Won't you sit on this and let us
carry you to the surface?

00:21:22.030 --> 00:21:26.451
I bet you miss breathing
the air up in the Soul Society.

00:21:29.121 --> 00:21:30.122
Pardon.

00:21:30.706 --> 00:21:33.208
I need to restrain you
before you are seated.

00:21:33.417 --> 00:21:34.710
Hey, what're you...

00:21:37.879 --> 00:21:39.923
Such gross carelessness.

00:21:40.674 --> 00:21:44.511
These restraints do not eliminate
my Spiritual Pressure.

00:21:45.012 --> 00:21:48.140
They can only keep it near me.

00:21:48.807 --> 00:21:52.853
I don't have to tell you
what will happen if you touch me.

00:21:54.855 --> 00:21:56.064
Shunsui Kyoraku.

00:21:57.399 --> 00:22:00.110
Even if I sat on that chair
and left this place,

00:22:00.861 --> 00:22:04.489
do you really think I would help
for the sake of the Soul Society?

00:22:05.115 --> 00:22:09.911
I'm not asking you to fight
for the sake of the Soul Society.

00:22:10.662 --> 00:22:11.705
However...

00:22:12.372 --> 00:22:17.544
I do believe
we share similar interests.

00:22:18.295 --> 00:22:21.381
You are truly an amusing man.

00:22:24.634 --> 00:22:27.846
Breathe the air, you ask?

00:22:29.056 --> 00:22:34.770
Of the pathetic Soul Society
about to be crushed by Yhwach?

00:22:39.066 --> 00:22:42.652
<i>An ache upon
an unsatisfying grayscale</i>

00:22:42.736 --> 00:22:46.615
<i>My confidence vanishes</i>

00:22:53.288 --> 00:22:54.706
<i>I turned regret into lies</i>

00:22:54.706 --> 00:22:56.708
<i>I ignored our chipped blades</i>

00:22:56.792 --> 00:22:58.418
<i>I worked overtime
just for maintenance</i>

00:22:58.502 --> 00:23:00.420
<i>But I knew all along</i>

00:23:00.462 --> 00:23:03.799
<i>that this faded color
was an irreversible law</i>

00:23:03.882 --> 00:23:05.759
<i>So I might as well pray</i>

00:23:05.801 --> 00:23:07.594
<i>There's no turning back now</i>

00:23:07.636 --> 00:23:09.471
<i>I thought I had made up my mind</i>

00:23:09.596 --> 00:23:11.264
<i>but I'm still haunted by
doubt and anxiety</i>

00:23:11.431 --> 00:23:12.974
<i>A bundle of emotions torn to shreds</i>

00:23:13.016 --> 00:23:14.810
<i>with nothing left for me to gain</i>

00:23:14.935 --> 00:23:18.772
<i>What's more important
than one's life</i>

00:23:18.814 --> 00:23:21.650
<i>is to shoulder that burden
to sever this monochrome</i>

00:23:21.650 --> 00:23:26.655
<i>I keep searching for the answer
to an unsolvable thesis</i>

00:23:26.738 --> 00:23:28.782
<i>while making choices until I die</i>

00:23:28.865 --> 00:23:32.911
<i>Then I remember where we came from</i>

00:23:32.994 --> 00:23:35.831
<i>and the lives
that could never interact</i>

00:23:35.914 --> 00:23:39.543
<i>No one is allowed to use the scale
since it falls apart in an instant</i>

00:23:39.626 --> 00:23:42.963
<i>So, what can I measure
ourselves against?</i>

00:23:43.046 --> 00:23:47.259
<i>Instead, I hold onto your words</i>

00:23:47.342 --> 00:23:50.095
<i>that gave my heart meaning</i>

00:23:50.178 --> 00:23:51.388
<i>It's always a paradox</i>

00:23:51.471 --> 00:23:53.473
<i>The moon waxes
with each regret and sadness</i>

00:23:53.598 --> 00:23:57.185
<i>The massive, unconquerable foe is
the darkness that dwells within me</i>

00:23:57.310 --> 00:23:58.895
<i>I forsook my pride and joy</i>

00:23:59.020 --> 00:24:00.647
<i>but I am still confounded
by this flock of imperfection</i>

00:24:00.730 --> 00:24:02.524
<i>Beyond that white and resentful
midnight sun</i>

00:24:02.649 --> 00:24:04.651
<i>awaits an illusion etched in black</i>

00:24:12.033 --> 00:24:15.328
<i>"I draw my bow,
fingers on the star"</i>

00:24:16.580 --> 00:24:19.624
<i>"against the moon
I thought I left behind."</i>

